## 2026-05-23 — Persian/Arabic digit normalization across CAPTCHA, OTP code, and phone
**Did:**
- Diagnosed: user reported CAPTCHA always failed with "کد امنیتی صحیح نیست". Root cause was Persian-keyboard input — the user typed `۲۳۴۵۶۷۸۹` while the CAPTCHA pool is ASCII `23456789…` and `.toUpperCase()` doesn't normalize digit code points. Same root cause would have bitten OTP code entry (`\D` filter strips Persian digits to empty string) and phone-number submission (backend's `normalize_iranian_mobile` rejects Persian-digit phones because `"۹" != "9"`).
- Added `toEnglishDigits(s)` helper in `frontend/src/App.tsx` covering Persian (`۰-۹`, U+06F0–06F9) and Arabic-Indic (`٠-٩`, U+0660–0669) digits.
- Applied at all three frontend sites: CAPTCHA validation, OTP code `onChange` (before the `\D` strip), and the phone/mobile values handed to `apiRegister`/`apiRequestLoginOtp`/`apiVerifyLoginOtp`/`apiRequestPasswordReset`/`apiCompletePasswordReset`.
- Mirrored on the backend: `app/domains/users/phone.py` now runs `_to_ascii_digits` before regex stripping, so even a non-frontend client (curl, mobile app) can send `۰۹۱۲۴۳۰۱۱۵۹` and we'll accept it.
- New test `test_register_accepts_persian_digit_phone` locks the backend behavior. 22/22 user-auth tests pass. Frontend `tsc --noEmit` clean.

**State:** still dirty (auth and OTP work from earlier today is uncommitted). New modifications: `frontend/src/App.tsx`, `backend/app/domains/users/phone.py`, `backend/tests/test_users.py`.

**Next:** back to the cart wire-up.

