## 2026-05-23 — Backend: DB-backed refresh tokens + logout + rotation (option 1)
**Did:**
- Bumped `REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRE_DAYS` default 7 → 10 (`app/config.py`, `.env.example`).
- Added `RefreshToken` model in `app/domains/users/models.py` (`user_id`, `token_hash`, `expires_at`, `revoked_at`, `created_at`).
- New Alembic migration `0007_refresh_tokens` — verified clean apply from empty DB; tables now: alembic_version, products, users, carts, cart_items, orders, order_items, payments, refresh_tokens.
- Added `hash_refresh_token` (sha256) in `app/security.py`; access + refresh JWTs now include a random `jti` claim so two tokens issued in the same second don't collide on the unique `token_hash` index.
- `users/service.py`: new `_issue_tokens` persists hashed refresh on login + on rotation. `refresh_tokens` now verifies signature → checks DB row (revoked/expired) → revokes-old + issues-new (rotation). New `logout(refresh_token)` revokes the row (idempotent for unknown tokens).
- `POST /auth/logout` route (204, body `{refresh_token}`).
- Tests in `tests/test_users.py`: added `test_refresh_rotates_token`, `test_logout_revokes_refresh`, `test_logout_unknown_token_is_idempotent`. All 11 user-auth tests pass.
- `ruff check . --fix` cleaned import ordering on the new migration (and incidentally on 4 pre-existing files); pytest still green afterward.
- Project memory saved: phone-OTP API is incoming (don't add `users.phone` column yet — wait for provider).

**State:** dirty — uncommitted changes across `backend/app/config.py`, `backend/app/security.py`, `backend/app/domains/users/{models,crud,service,router}.py`, `backend/tests/test_users.py`, `backend/.env.example`; new file `backend/alembic/versions/0007_refresh_tokens.py`. Ruff also touched import ordering in `alembic/env.py`, `alembic/versions/0003_users.py`, `0005_payments.py`, `0006_product_marketing_fields.py` — drive-by formatting fixes, no behavior change. Backend venv was rebuilt with python3.11 (system python had moved to 3.12 and broke it).

